reason.tex:
\begin{align}
			  \cos 2\theta &= \cos^2\theta - \sin^2\theta \\
			  &=-(\sin^2\theta - \cos^2\theta) \\
			  \therefore \sin^2\frac{x}{2} - \cos^2\frac{x}{2} &= 
			  -\cos \left(2\cdot\frac{x}{2}\right) = -\cos x
			\end{align} \\
			\begin{align}
			  &\implies \int_0^\pi \left(\sin^2\frac{x}{2} -\cos^2\frac{x}{2}\right) \cdot dx \\
			  &= \underbrace{-\int_0^\pi\cos x\cdot dx = \int_\pi^0\cos x\cdot dx}
			  _{\int_a^b f(x) dx = -\int_b^a f(x)dx}
			\end{align} \\
			\text{Compare }\int_\pi^0\cos x\cdot dx\text{ with }\int_a^b\cos Mx\cdot dx, \\
			\text{and one can see that }M = 1, a = \pi\text{ and }b = 0.
